message.content:
<OUTPUT_TEXT>

Dear Students,

I hope this message finds you well. As we continue on our educational journey, I would like to share some important instructions regarding our forthcoming learning sessions.

1. Individual Instructions: There will be times when you will be instructed individually. This means that I will be teaching you one-on-one. During these sessions, I will focus on your individual learning needs, strengths, and areas for improvement. You are encouraged to ask questions, share your thoughts, and actively participate in these sessions.

2. Group Instructions: At other times, we will be learning as a group. In these sessions, we will be working together to solve problems, discuss topics, and learn from each other. It is important that you respect your classmates' ideas and opinions during these group discussions. Remember, everyone has something valuable to contribute.

3. Lectures: Some of our lessons will be delivered in the form of lectures. During these sessions, I will present information on a specific topic. You are expected to listen carefully, take notes, and ask questions if something is not clear.

4. Discussions: We will also have discussion-based lessons. In these sessions, we will talk about different topics, share our ideas, and learn from each other. It's important to come to these discussions prepared, having read or studied the necessary materials.

5. Demonstrations: Lastly, there will be times when I will demonstrate a concept or skill. These demonstrations are designed to help you understand how things work in a practical sense. You should observe these demonstrations carefully and try to apply what you learn in your own work.

Remember, learning is a journey that we are all on together. Let's make the most of each session and help each other grow. 

Best Regards,

[Your Name]

</OUTPUT_TEXT>
